Yes. Usually the lower div CS classes (CS61ABC, CS70) are safe to Phase II.

(Edit:) Also a lot more people than you expect will drop after the first few weeks or so. I took it Fall 2015, and I forgot the numbers exactly but something like 200 people dropped within the first 2 months. If he/she can't get in directly, they will almost definitely get in on the wait list.
Yes. Usually the lower div CS classes (CS61ABC, CS70) are safe to Phase II.
Yes. Usually the lower div CS classes (CS61ABC, CS70) are safe to Phase II.

We cannot guarantee seats for anyone in phase 2, but we have historically tried to accommodate students prioritized here (http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml?_ga=1.84099098.2007352052.1445915650 )including first and 2nd year L&S CS undeclared students. Of course, being on the waitlist by definition means that there is no guarantee and students who sign up later will probably have to be more flexible about which lab/discussion pairs they choose.

We cannot guarantee seats for anyone in phase 2, but we have historically tried to accommodate our L&S CS intended students. CS 61A may be smaller this year, so it is not a guarantee. Michael-David Sasson is on vacation this week so he may make some edits to my response when he returns.

Asking for a friend who is an undeclared freshman in l&s: would it be safe to phase two this class? In previous years, it has expanded, but will it expand to hold everyone this year and would a phase 2 for this class still let you get it? Thanks!
